
[1]candid

   CANDID, a.

   1. White.

   2. Fair; open; frank; ingenuous; free from undue bias; disposed to
   think and judge according to truth and justice, or without partiality
   or prejudice; applied to persons.

   3. Fair; just; impartial; applied to things; as a candid view, or
   construction.
